            <thetext>The &quot;menu&quot; element was introduced as part of the new interactive elements in HTML5. The &quot;contextmenu&quot; attribute assigns a context menu to an element and may reference menus defined with the &quot;menu&quot; element. This way, it is possible to add items to the native context menu.

Currently, only Firefox 8 supports this feature.

Demo: https://bug617528.bugzilla.mozilla.org/attachment.cgi?id=554309
Spec: http://www.w3.org/TR/html5/interactive-elements.html#menus
Bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=617528

We should provide a way to add items to the native context menu of a given widget easily.</thetext>
